    <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/11/16/playing-around-with-dall-e-to-create-images-of-future-learning-spaces/">
        <h2 class="post-title">Playing Around With DALL-E to Create Images of Future Learning Spaces</h2>
        
        
        
    </a>

    <p class="post-meta">
        <span class="post-meta">
  
  
  <i class="fas fa-calendar"></i>&nbsp;November 16, 2023
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-clock"></i>&nbsp;3&nbsp;minutes
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-book"></i>&nbsp;508&nbsp;words
  
  
  
</span>


    </p>
    <div class="post-entry">
        
        Inspired by Benj Edwards&rsquo; post on Ars Technica this morning, I wanted to try out the latest version of DALL-E that&rsquo;s integrated into ChatGPT 4 Turboâ„¢, to see what it could create to visualize potential future learning spaces.
I started off with a basic &ldquo;Create an image of a video game depicting students exploring classrooms and informal learning spaces. Cinematic, 8K, studio lighting.&rdquo;
ðŸ¤– - AI-Generated Content via DALL-EInteresting. Chalkboards, but sure.
        <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/11/16/playing-around-with-dall-e-to-create-images-of-future-learning-spaces/" class="post-read-more">Read More</a>
        
        
        
		
		
