            <article class="post-preview">
    <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/11/13/rethinking-about-generative-ai/">
        <h2 class="post-title">Rethinking About Generative AI</h2>
        
        
        
    </a>

    <p class="post-meta">
        <span class="post-meta">
  
  
  <i class="fas fa-calendar"></i>&nbsp;November 13, 2023
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-clock"></i>&nbsp;23&nbsp;minutes
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-book"></i>&nbsp;4760&nbsp;words
  
  
  
</span>


    </p>
    <div class="post-entry">
        
        This post was originally going to be part of a series exploring the topic, but if I take that approach I&rsquo;ll probably never actually make time to write each post in the series, so here&rsquo;s an omnibus &ldquo;I need to think about this stuff and writing a blog post is the best way to formalize my thinking.&rdquo;
We&rsquo;ve all been trying to figure out generative AI since ChatGPT was launched almost 1 year ago.
        <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/11/13/rethinking-about-generative-ai/" class="post-read-more">Read More</a>
        
        
        
		
		
