            <article class="post-preview">
    <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/07/04/presenting-to-the-association-of-university-architects/">
        <h2 class="post-title">Presenting to the Association of University Architects</h2>
        
        
        
    </a>

    <p class="post-meta">
        <span class="post-meta">
  
  
  <i class="fas fa-calendar"></i>&nbsp;July 4, 2023
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-clock"></i>&nbsp;13&nbsp;minutes
  
  
    &nbsp;|&nbsp;<i class="fas fa-book"></i>&nbsp;2564&nbsp;words
  
  
  
</span>


    </p>
    <div class="post-entry">
        
        I&rsquo;d intended to quickly write this post to reflect on the session, but it&rsquo;s stayed in my drafts pile for a couple of weeks now so I&rsquo;m going to share what I can remember. I&rsquo;ll likely be misremembering some of the details of the session, but this should hit the highlights at least.
Recently, I had the absolute pleasure to be invited to co-present at the 67th Annual Association of University Architects Conference, conveniently hosted this year in Calgary, and even more conveniently having one day&rsquo;s sessions housed within the Taylor Institute for Teaching and Learning.
        <a href="https://darcynorman.net/2023/07/04/presenting-to-the-association-of-university-architects/" class="post-read-more">Read More</a>
        
        
        
		
		
			<hr><p><em>Images used in this post:</em></p>
		
